This rotated region3 module is a bit different than the one I previously wrote. This uses GJK to do the collision calculations and
as such does not calculate the minimum translation vector. In addition it does not calculate the intersection points anymore either.
I don't think that had much place in a rotated region3 module.

""desc"": ""   In the heart of medieval England, a legendary outlaw emerged from the depths of Sherwood Forest—Robin Hood. This is the timeless tale of a courageous and cunning hero who fought against injustice, championed the oppressed, and became a symbol of hope for the common people. Robin Hood, a skilled archer and swordsman, found himself on the wrong side of the law after a series of events led him to rebel against the tyrannical rule of Prince John and the corrupt Sheriff of Nottingham. With a band of loyal followers known as his Merry Men, including the charismatic Little John, the nimble Friar Tuck, and the fearless Maid Marian, Robin Hood embarked on a daring quest to restore justice and return power to the rightful king, Richard the Lionheart. Living in Sherwood Forest, Robin Hood and his Merry Men became renowned for their daring escapades. They would often disguise themselves, concealing their true identities, as they robbed from the rich and corrupt, redistributing the ill-gotten wealth to the poor and downtrodden. Their exploits made them beloved figures among the common folk, who regarded Robin Hood as a hero fighting for their rights and well-being.\n   The Sheriff of Nottingham, however, was determined to capture Robin Hood and bring him to justice. Countless attempts were made to ensnare the outlaw, but Robin's quick wit, sharpshooting skills, and knowledge of the forest always ensured his escape. He used the natural surroundings of Sherwood Forest to his advantage, disappearing into the depths of the woodland whenever the authorities closed in. Amidst the battles and escapades, a deep and enduring love blossomed between Robin Hood and Maid Marian. Their relationship symbolized a unity of purpose and a shared commitment to the cause. Maid Marian, a strong and resourceful woman, became an integral part of Robin Hood's band, embodying the spirit of resistance and unwavering loyalty. The legend of Robin Hood reached its pinnacle when King Richard the Lionheart returned from the Crusades to reclaim his rightful throne. Robin Hood and his Merry Men played a pivotal role in aiding the king's return, as their deeds had captured the imagination and support of the people. In a climactic showdown, Robin Hood and his band fought alongside King Richard, defeating Prince John and the Sheriff of Nottingham, ensuring the restoration of justice and peace to the land.\n   Robin Hood's exploits were celebrated throughout the kingdom, and his name became synonymous with honor, valor, and the fight against oppression. Even after his passing, the legend of Robin Hood lived on, inspiring countless tales, ballads, and works of art that celebrated his courage and indomitable spirit.""

column1: ""name"": ""The Trojan War: The Fall of Troy"",

""desc"": ""   In ancient times, a war raged on the shores of Troy, a city fortified by high walls and destined for a tragic fate. This is the epic tale of the Trojan War, a conflict that would shape the course of history and inspire countless tales of heroism and betrayal. The story begins with a beautiful mortal woman named Helen, wife of King Menelaus of Sparta. Helen's extraordinary beauty caught the attention of Prince Paris of Troy, who, under the influence of the goddess Aphrodite, eloped with her, igniting a spark that would set the world ablaze. Furious at the audacity of Paris, Menelaus summoned the kings and heroes of Greece, forging an alliance to retrieve Helen and avenge the insult. Among the most revered warriors were the mighty Achilles, the cunning Odysseus, and the valiant Ajax. Under the leadership of King Agamemnon of Mycenae, they set sail for Troy, their hearts filled with a thirst for glory and retribution.\n   The Greek forces amassed outside the walls of Troy, a seemingly impenetrable fortress defended by the brave Trojan warriors. The Trojan prince Hector, a formidable warrior and protector of his city, emerged as their greatest champion. With the guidance of their wise and revered king, Priam, and the assistance of the gods Apollo and Aphrodite, the Trojans believed they could withstand any assault. For ten long years, the Greeks besieged the city of Troy, launching relentless attacks. The battlefield witnessed countless heroic acts, with both sides suffering losses and victories. The legends of Achilles' rage, Hector's bravery, and Odysseus' cunning strategy spread far and wide. But it was the ruse of the infamous Trojan Horse that would ultimately seal Troy's fate. In a stroke of genius, Odysseus conceived a plan to construct a massive wooden horse, seemingly an offering of surrender. Concealed within its hollow belly were Greek warriors, waiting for the cover of night to unleash destruction upon the unsuspecting Trojans. Deceived by the apparent gift and the apparent departure of the Greek forces, the Trojans joyously celebrated their victory. Under the cover of darkness, the Greek warriors emerged, opening the gates of Troy to their waiting comrades. The city erupted in chaos and bloodshed as the Greeks pillaged and set fire to Troy, reducing the once-proud city to ashes.\n   In the aftermath, Troy lay in ruins, its defenders defeated and its people scattered. The survivors faced a future filled with sorrow and loss. The Trojan War had reached its bitter conclusion, leaving a legacy of tragedy and lessons that would echo through the ages.""

LkM74CSS,King Arthur and the Knights of the Round Table,AhmadXploit,Dart,Thursday 13th of July 2023 06:00:44 AM CDT,[
""name"": ""King Arthur and the Knights of the Round Table"",

""desc"": ""   In the realm of ancient Britain, a legend was born—the tale of King Arthur and the Knights of the Round Table. This epic story is steeped in heroism, chivalry, and the pursuit of justice. It begins with the young Arthur, an unsuspecting boy destined for greatness. Merlin the magician, wise and enigmatic, guided Arthur throughout his childhood, concealing the truth of his royal lineage. When Arthur grew to adulthood, the sword Excalibur revealed his true identity as the rightful heir to the throne. With Excalibur in hand, Arthur claimed his birthright and became the King of Camelot.
   Seeking to establish a realm of unity and equality, King Arthur instituted a unique round table at which his knights would convene. This round table ensured that no knight held a superior position, symbolizing the equality and fairness that Arthur wished to uphold in his kingdom. Arthur's knights were renowned for their valor, honor, and unwavering loyalty. Sir Lancelot, the most celebrated of Arthur's knights, embodied the ideals of chivalry, while Sir Gawain, Sir Percival, and Sir Galahad were equally esteemed for their courage and noble deeds. Together, they formed the brotherhood that would be forever remembered as the Knights of the Round Table. Their adventures were many, as they embarked on quests to uphold justice and protect the realm. They faced formidable foes, battled fearsome beasts, and defended the weak against tyranny. Their code of chivalry guided their actions, emphasizing the importance of truth, loyalty, and compassion.
   However, darkness lurked within the heart of Camelot. Mordred, Arthur's treacherous nephew, grew envious of his uncle's power and sought to overthrow him. Mordred's machinations set in motion a series of events that led to the downfall of Camelot. In the final confrontation, the Battle of Camlann, King Arthur faced off against Mordred. Their clash was fierce, and both were mortally wounded. As the battle raged on, the Round Table shattered, symbolizing the fracturing of the ideals they once held dear.
   With his last breaths, Arthur entrusted his trusted knight, Sir Bedivere, with the task of returning Excalibur to the Lady of the Lake. Bedivere obeyed, throwing the sword into the waters, where a hand rose from the lake to claim it. As Excalibur vanished beneath the surface, Arthur was taken to the mystical island of Avalon, where he would rest until Britain's time of need. The Knights of the Round Table scattered, their noble order disbanded. The once glorious kingdom of Camelot fell into ruin, and the memory of King Arthur and his valiant knights faded into legend. Yet, the ideals they embodied—honor, courage, and justice—remained etched in the hearts of those who heard their tale.""

0rQWdSTm,The Legend of Atlantis,AhmadXploit,Dart,Thursday 13th of July 2023 05:51:44 AM CDT,[

""desc"": ""   Long ago, in the depths of the ocean, there existed a magnificent and prosperous city known as Atlantis. The legend of Atlantis has captivated imaginations for centuries, and its story is shrouded in mystery and wonder. This tale recounts the mythical city's rise, its grandeur, and the tragic events that led to its ultimate demise. According to ancient texts, Atlantis was believed to have been a powerful and advanced civilization, far ahead of its time. It was said to be located beyond the Pillars of Hercules, now known as the Strait of Gibraltar, and nestled in a vast island surrounded by the vast ocean. The Atlanteans were known for their extraordinary knowledge of science, engineering, and arts. They possessed technology that surpassed any civilization of the time. The city boasted magnificent architecture, with towering structures made of crystal-clear quartz and ornate carvings that depicted their rich history.\n   At the heart of Atlantis was a wise and just ruler named King Atlas. He governed the city with compassion, seeking the prosperity and well-being of his people. Under his reign, Atlantis flourished, and its citizens enjoyed a harmonious existence. But as time passed, a gradual shift occurred in the Atlantean society. The pursuit of material wealth and power began to overshadow the values that once defined them. Greed and ambition took hold of some, and corruption seeped into the once-virtuous city. It was during this time of unrest that a catastrophic event struck Atlantis. The skies darkened, the earth trembled, and the ocean rose with fury. Massive earthquakes and powerful tidal waves engulfed the city, leaving devastation in their wake. Atlantis, once a thriving metropolis, was swallowed by the ocean's depths. Legends say that Atlantis vanished beneath the waves, disappearing into the abyss forever. Some believe that the gods, witnessing the city's descent into decadence, punished Atlantis for its hubris. Others suggest that a cataclysmic natural disaster led to the city's demise.\n   Whatever the cause, Atlantis became a lost city, sinking to the ocean's floor, its secrets buried beneath layers of water and time. Tales of Atlantis were passed down through generations, creating a mythical legacy that continues to intrigue scholars and explorers to this day. Many adventurers have embarked on expeditions, hoping to uncover the truth and rediscover the fabled city. Some claim to have found remnants of Atlantis, while others dismiss these claims as mere speculation. The mystery surrounding Atlantis remains unsolved, leaving us to wonder if the city truly existed or if it was simply a product of human imagination.""
